<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,1889,2022]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Second and subsequent instar caterpillars have scattered long setae; the body and setae are covered with white waxy powder, giving the impression of some fungus-infested body (
<figureCitation box="[917,1062,1925,1950]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="41.[151,250,597,619]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,572]" captionTargetId="figure-332@41.[151,1436,195,572]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 39. Stage 1 shelter of Gretna balenge with instars 1 and 2 caterpillars, collected on Eremospatha sp., Chikonke stream, north-west Zambia [TCEC]. 1, instar 1, dorsal view, 18 May 2000; 2, instar 2, dorsolateral view, 21 May 2000." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920910" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920910/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Figures 39.2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1074,1156,1925,1950]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1438,1460]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,702,1414]" captionTargetId="figure-341@41.[151,1436,702,1414]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 40. Leaf Shelter and final instar caterpillars of Gretna balenge balenge. 1, Leaf shelter in situ on Dypsis lutescens, Port Harcourt, Nigeria [© D. Motshagen]; 2, caterpillar, lateral view, as 1 [© D. Motshagen]; 3, caterpillars in dorsal (above) and dorsolateral view (below), with most of white wax removed, collected on Eremospatha sp., Chikonke stream, north-west Zambia, 17 May 2000 [TCEC]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920912" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920912/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">40.2–3</figureCitation>
). Much of the white wax was removed to reveal the underlying pattern of the final instar caterpillar in 
<figureCitation box="[1011,1143,1961,1986]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1438,1460]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,702,1414]" captionTargetId="figure-341@41.[151,1436,702,1414]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 40. Leaf Shelter and final instar caterpillars of Gretna balenge balenge. 1, Leaf shelter in situ on Dypsis lutescens, Port Harcourt, Nigeria [© D. Motshagen]; 2, caterpillar, lateral view, as 1 [© D. Motshagen]; 3, caterpillars in dorsal (above) and dorsolateral view (below), with most of white wax removed, collected on Eremospatha sp., Chikonke stream, north-west Zambia, 17 May 2000 [TCEC]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920912" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920912/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Figure 40.3</figureCitation>
; white with an interrupted dark dorsal line and brown head.
</paragraph>
